[[TITLE]] The Aster Filesystem
[[TAGS]] aster filesystem fs file directory structure
[[DESCRIPTION]] The table of contents and overview of the AsterOS Manual.
[[CONTENTS]]
Aster uses its own filesystem that lacks the traditional file extensions and
categorizations inherent in other file systems, opting instead for a tag-based
approach. Each file can have up to 255 "tags", which are little categories that
will help you find any given file when also given information about its name.
Because of this system, organizational structures can appear naturally as
collections of files with similar tags.

The list of all currently defined tags is as follows;

[[LIST]]
-- system: System files.
-- hidden: Hidden files to not be displayed by default.
-- source: A source code file.
-- include: An "include" or interface file.
-- executable: An executable file.
-- script: An interpreted file.
[[ENDLIST]]

All other tag indices are considered "reserved", and should neither be used or
defined by any application, for the purpose of forward-facing compatibility.
